AND I KNOW PEOPLE WHO'LL
PAY BIG BUCKS TO WATCH
A KICKBOXER LIKE YOU IN ACTION.

19:14.588 --> 19:17.895
AND YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT AMATEUR RULES
OR DISQUALIFICATIONS.

19:18.679 --> 19:20.202
THE WINNER WINS.

19:21.072 --> 19:22.161
-HOW MUCH?

19:25.860 --> 19:28.645
-TAKE IT.
GO GET YOURSELF
A GOOD MEAL.

19:28.776 --> 19:31.735
GET CLEANED UP.
YOU MEET ME HERE
TOMORROW AT FIVE.

19:32.910 --> 19:36.131
AND YOU COME READY TO WIN.
THERE'LL BE FIVE MORE OF THOSE
WAITING FOR YOU.

19:40.570 --> 19:42.137
YOU'RE GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT, KID.

19:55.411 --> 19:57.196
-ALAIN, THESE ARE SO BEAUTIFUL.

20:00.199 --> 20:02.070
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I COULD LOOK THIS WAY.

20:02.984 --> 20:06.466
-THEY ARE BEAUTIFUL PICTURES.
I'M GLAD YOU LIKE THEM.

20:08.381 --> 20:11.079
BUT UNFORTUNATELY,
THEY ARE NOT OF YOU.

20:12.602 --> 20:13.690
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

20:21.698 --> 20:24.223
-THERE IS SO MUCH MORE
INSIDE OF YOU.

20:25.789 --> 20:27.704
YOUR FIERY SPIRIT...

20:29.793 --> 20:31.273
YOUR PASSION...

20:32.231 --> 20:33.536
YOUR SENSUALITY...

20:35.234 --> 20:38.280
THAT IS WHAT I NEED
TO CAPTURE ON FILM.

20:38.411 --> 20:41.936
THAT IS WHAT YOU MUST
ALLOW ME TO SEE, C.J.

20:44.155 --> 20:47.158
-ALAIN, I DON'T KNOW.
-IF YOU TRUST ME, C.J.,

20:48.116 --> 20:49.726
I CAN DRAW IT OUT OF YOU.

20:49.857 --> 20:51.511
DO YOU TRUST ME?

20:53.556 --> 20:55.558
-YES. IT'S JUST--
-SHH, SHH, SHH.

20:55.689 --> 20:57.908
COME WITH ME.

21:02.435 --> 21:03.566
COME DOWN TO YOUR KNEES.

21:07.788 --> 21:10.181
NOW, KISS ME.
-WHAT?

21:10.312 --> 21:13.184
-C.J., YOU HAVE TO KEEP
TRUSTING ME.

21:13.837 --> 21:17.798
JUST PRETEND LIKE MY MOUTH
IS THE LENS OF THE CAMERA.

21:19.539 --> 21:20.757
-THIS IS CRAZY.

21:20.888 --> 21:22.672
-YOU CAN DO IT.

21:37.557 --> 21:38.949
TOMORROW...

21:39.080 --> 21:40.995
WE WILL TAKE MORE PICTURES.

21:42.562 --> 21:45.173
JUST YOU AND I, ALONE.

21:45.913 --> 21:47.262
NO ONE ELSE.

21:49.612 --> 21:51.135
AND YOU WILL OPEN UP TO ME

21:51.266 --> 21:53.616
AS NEVER BEFORE
TO ANY OTHER MAN...

21:55.575 --> 21:56.750
NOT EVEN YOURSELF.

22:00.101 --> 22:01.798
[SPEAKS FRENCH]

22:29.522 --> 22:30.740
-STEVE!

22:30.871 --> 22:32.481
HI.
-HI.

22:34.178 --> 22:36.355
-I WAS HOPING
I COULD FIND YOU HERE.

22:38.313 --> 22:40.097
LOOK, UM...

22:40.228 --> 22:42.883
I JUST WANTED TO SAY
SORRY ABOUT YESTERDAY.

22:43.013 --> 22:44.624
-WELL, DON'T BE.

22:44.754 --> 22:46.887
I MEAN, I SHOULD BE THE ONE
APOLOGIZING TO YOU.

22:47.017 --> 22:48.715
-NO, I MEAN,
YOU WERE JUST UPSET.

22:48.845 --> 22:51.152
-YEAH, WELL,
I HAVE THIS REAL PROBLEM
WITH MY TEMPER.

22:51.805 --> 22:53.328
I MEAN, YOU'VE SEEN IT.

22:53.459 --> 22:55.374
-STEVE, WHAT ARE YOU
SO ANGRY ABOUT?

22:58.028 --> 23:00.204
I'M SORRY. YOU DON'T
HAVE TO ANSWER THAT.

23:03.512 --> 23:05.340
-MY DAD USED TO BEAT UP
MY MOM A LOT.

23:07.124 --> 23:09.518
EVERY TIME I TRIED TO HELP HER,
I'D GET HIT, TOO.

23:11.259 --> 23:13.914
YOU KNOW, IT SEEMS LIKE
I SPENT MY WHOLE CHILDHOOD
GETTING BEAT ON...

23:15.481 --> 23:16.960
OR BEATING UP ON SOMEBODY.

23:18.571 --> 23:20.486
YOU KNOW,
UNTIL I STARTED KICKBOXING.

23:20.616 --> 23:22.444
I MEAN, IT REALLY HELPS ME.

23:22.575 --> 23:24.577
-WELL, THERE MUST BE
OTHER THINGS YOU CAN DO.

23:24.707 --> 23:27.493
-LOOK, YOU'RE A GOOD SWIMMER,
SO YOU BECAME A LIFEGUARD.

23:27.623 --> 23:30.191
I CAN FIGHT.
THAT'S WHAT I DO.

23:30.321 --> 23:33.194
-[CAR HORN HONKS]
-THORN, LET'S GO!

23:34.064 --> 23:36.240
-UM, LOOK, I GOTTA GO.
I'LL SEE YOU LATER?

23:38.199 --> 23:41.245
-STEVE, WAIT!
WHERE ARE YOU GOING
WITH THAT GUY?

23:41.376 --> 23:43.596
HE'S BAD NEWS.

23:43.726 --> 23:45.511
-NO, THIS IS THE GUY
THAT GOT ME THE FIGHT
WHERE I CAN MAKE SOME MONEY.

23:46.337 --> 23:47.251
WISH ME LUCK.

23:48.209 --> 23:49.819
-WAIT A MINUTE.

23:49.950 --> 23:52.779
I WANT TO GO WITH YOU.
-I THOUGHT YOU HATED KICKBOXING.

23:53.780 --> 23:55.738
-WELL, I GUESS
I CHANGED MY MIND.

24:07.750 --> 24:09.535
-COME DOWN TO THE SAND.
-[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

24:09.665 --> 24:10.536
-SLOWLY.

24:10.666 --> 24:12.102
-[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

24:12.233 --> 24:14.409
-I WANT YOU TO IMAGINE
YOU ARE A SERPENT...

24:15.062 --> 24:17.020
-[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]
-A SNAKE...

24:17.760 --> 24:20.197
-[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]
-CRAWLING ACROSS THE HOT SAND.

24:20.981 --> 24:24.593
-OUI. VOILA.
-[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

24:26.073 --> 24:28.728
-FEEL THE HEAT OF THE SAND
ON YOUR BODY.

24:28.858 --> 24:31.774
-[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

24:31.905 --> 24:33.472
-YES.

24:34.821 --> 24:35.822
DESTROY ME.

24:57.321 --> 24:59.193
-IT'S OKAY. THESE PEOPLE
ARE FRIENDS OF MINE.

24:59.323 --> 25:00.324
-ALL RIGHT, SIR. GO AHEAD.

25:07.941 --> 25:10.291
-IS THIS A RESTAURANT?
-USED TO BE.

25:10.421 --> 25:12.162
NOW, THEY JUST RENT IT OUT
FOR PRIVATE PARTIES.

25:22.738 --> 25:24.479
-THIS PLACE IS UNREAL.

25:24.610 --> 25:26.786
-WELL, LET ME INTRODUCE YOU
TO THE MAN WHO MADE IT REAL.

25:26.916 --> 25:29.876
KAMEL, THIS IS STEVE THORN.
-HI, SIR.

25:31.573 --> 25:34.184
-YOU SEE?
YOU MUST BE ALWAYS ALERT,

25:34.881 --> 25:36.622
INSIDE THE RING OR OUTSIDE IT.

25:36.752 --> 25:38.711
-YES, SIR. I'LL TRY
TO REMEMBER THAT.

25:53.508 --> 25:54.422
-C.J.!

25:55.292 --> 25:56.163
HOW'D IT GO?

26:04.824 --> 26:06.477
WHAT HAPPENED?
THAT JERK TRY SOMETHING?

26:06.608 --> 26:07.478
-NO.

26:09.393 --> 26:11.221
-THEN, WHAT'S THE MATTER?
WHY ARE YOU SO UPSET?

26:13.484 --> 26:15.225
-I THINK I GOT
THE COVER GIRL JOB.

26:16.487 --> 26:18.141
-I THOUGHT THAT'S
WHAT YOU WANTED.

26:18.272 --> 26:19.708
-I DON'T KNOW.

26:20.840 --> 26:24.365
IF I BECOME HIS MODEL,
ALAIN SAID I HAVE TO GIVE UP
BEING A LIFEGUARD.

26:26.933 --> 26:28.412
YOU GUYS ARE MY FAMILY.

26:29.892 --> 26:32.982
-C.J., IF THAT'S WHAT
YOU REALLY WANT,

26:33.548 --> 26:34.897
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO GIVE UP ANYTHING.

26:35.028 --> 26:36.377
WHY DON'T YOU JUST DO BOTH?

26:36.507 --> 26:39.728
-YEAH, BUT THE THING IS,
I REALLY WANT HIM.

26:42.383 --> 26:43.819
MITCH, I THINK I'M IN LOVE.

26:44.559 --> 26:47.867
-OH, NO, C.J.
COME ON. NOT AGAIN.
YOU JUST MET THE GUY.

26:47.997 --> 26:51.566
-I DON'T KNOW. HE JUST--
HE BRINGS OUT FEELINGS IN ME
I NEVER KNEW I HAD.

26:51.697 --> 26:53.176
-YOU SAY THAT EVERY TIME.

26:53.307 --> 26:54.874
-NO, THIS TIME'S DIFFERENT.

26:56.658 --> 26:59.095
I'VE NEVER FELT THE THINGS
HE MAKES ME FEEL.

27:00.662 --> 27:02.490
HE REALLY BELIEVES IN ME.

27:03.491 --> 27:05.580
-LOOK, I'M SORRY.
I GOTTA GO.

27:07.060 --> 27:09.671
DO ME A FAVOR, WILL YA?
TAKE YOUR TIME.

27:09.802 --> 27:11.542
DON'T MAKE ANY RASH DECISIONS.

27:14.633 --> 27:16.896
-BUT I NEED TO LET HIM KNOW
BY 3:00 TOMORROW.

27:17.026 --> 27:19.420
-[LAUGHS]
-MITCH, TELL ME WHAT TO DO!

27:20.987 --> 27:24.120
-C.J., YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO DECIDE THIS ONE ON YOUR OWN.

27:25.208 --> 27:27.646
BUT JUST REMEMBER,
I BELIEVE IN YOU, TOO.

27:47.404 --> 27:49.929
-HOW YOU DOING, AL?
-ALL RIGHT, SIR, THANK YOU.

28:16.869 --> 28:18.044
-NEXT BOUT.

28:29.533 --> 28:32.145
-COME ON, GET HIM!
-YES, THAT'S IT!

28:32.275 --> 28:33.363
-[PEOPLE CHEERING]

28:35.148 --> 28:36.715
-HARDER! COME ON!

28:39.108 --> 28:41.589
-HE'S NOT GOING UNDER.
FAKING AND PUNCHING.

28:41.720 --> 28:43.678
-FORGET ABOUT IT.
HE'S GOT NO CHANCE.

28:52.861 --> 28:55.908
-I KNOW. IT'S LIKE
THE DAMN COLOSSEUM IN ROME.

28:57.213 --> 28:58.780
-WHY ARE YOU
DOING THIS TO STEVE?

28:58.911 --> 29:00.913
-I'M HELPING HIM.
HE NEEDS THE MONEY.

29:02.349 --> 29:05.874
AND BESIDES, DO YOU KNOW
HOW MUCH THESE GUYS TIP
IF THEY LIKE A FIGHTER?

29:06.005 --> 29:08.007
[SCOFFS]
-ENOUGH TO PAY
HIS HOSPITAL BILLS?

29:08.137 --> 29:11.097
-WELL, LET'S HOPE SO.
HE'LL BE FIGHTING ME.

29:23.283 --> 29:25.241
-[FANS CHEERING]

29:30.464 --> 29:32.422
-STEVE, YOU CANNOT
GO THROUGH WITH THIS.

29:32.553 --> 29:34.033
-DON'T WORRY.
IT'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

29:34.163 --> 29:35.904
-NO, YOU ARE FIGHTING BRANSON.

29:36.035 --> 29:39.690
-WHAT? ARE YOU SURE?
-YEAH, HE JUST TOLD ME HIMSELF.

29:39.821 --> 29:41.605
COME ON, HURRY.
GET YOUR CLOTHES.

29:41.736 --> 29:43.520
WE HAVE TO GET OUT OF HERE.

29:45.131 --> 29:46.915
-NO, YOU DON'T.
-LOOK, MR. BRANSON,

29:47.046 --> 29:49.091
WE'RE NOT EVEN
IN THE SAME WEIGHT CATEGORY.

29:49.222 --> 29:51.180
-IT DOESN'T MATTER HERE.
-LOOK, HE'S NOT FIGHTING.

29:51.311 --> 29:53.008
HE'S LEAVING NOW.

29:53.139 --> 29:54.618
-YEAH? I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

29:55.358 --> 29:57.056
I DON'T REALLY WANT
TO FIGHT YOU, EITHER.

29:57.186 --> 29:59.493
SO, MAYBE THERE'S A WAY
WE CAN ALL WORK TOGETHER.

29:59.623 --> 30:01.625
FIND ME ANOTHER OPPONENT.

30:04.237 --> 30:05.542
-WHY WON'T YOU TALK ABOUT IT?

30:05.673 --> 30:08.154
-BECAUSE.
-WELL, YOU SHOULD.

30:08.850 --> 30:11.200
-WHY?
-BECAUSE.

30:13.681 --> 30:15.248
-FINE.

30:15.378 --> 30:16.423
-SO, WHAT HAPPENED?

30:17.685 --> 30:19.165
-BRANSON WAS A STUDENT OF MINE.

30:20.166 --> 30:23.082
HAND-TO-HAND COMBAT
IN THE NAVY SEALS.

30:24.300 --> 30:26.302
THIS GUY COULD
NEVER HANDLE LOSING...

30:27.695 --> 30:28.957
EVEN IN TRAINING.

30:29.697 --> 30:31.177
ONE DAY, HE GOT INVOLVED
IN A FIGHT...

30:31.873 --> 30:33.832
HE WAS OBVIOUSLY LOSING,

30:33.962 --> 30:35.181
BUT HE WOULDN'T QUIT.

30:36.051 --> 30:38.749
CAUGHT THE GUY OFF GUARD,
FRACTURED HIS ARM IN TWO PLACES,

30:39.359 --> 30:40.447
AND HE LAUGHED ABOUT IT.

30:42.014 --> 30:45.582
SO, I WROTE HIM UP,
AND THEY DISCHARGED HIM.

30:46.714 --> 30:47.846
BUT HE WOULDN'T LEAVE THE BASE.

30:48.890 --> 30:50.892
HE KEPT COMING AFTER ME,

30:51.023 --> 30:52.807
SAYING HE WANTED TO FIGHT ME,

30:52.938 --> 30:55.854
MAN-TO-MAN,
TO THE DEATH, HE SAID.

30:56.593 --> 30:57.725
-[PHONE RINGS]

30:58.944 --> 31:02.208
-FINALLY, MPS DRAGGED HIM AWAY.

31:02.730 --> 31:04.427
-[RINGING CONTINUES]
-THAT WAS THE LAST...

31:04.558 --> 31:06.777
I HEARD OF HIM...

31:06.908 --> 31:08.692
UNTIL THE OTHER DAY
ON THE BEACH.

31:08.823 --> 31:10.303
-[RINGING CONTINUES]

31:10.433 --> 31:12.261
-SOMEBODY GET THE PHONE!

31:16.570 --> 31:18.702
BAYWATCH.
-MITCH, IT'S SUMMER.

31:18.833 --> 31:22.097
-YEAH, SUMMER, WHAT'S UP?
-YOU ARE, OLD BUDDY.

31:23.316 --> 31:26.667
YOU'D BETTER COME ON OVER HERE,
AND MAKE IT FAST. COME ALONE.

31:26.797 --> 31:28.538
-BRANSON,
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON?

31:29.365 --> 31:31.019
-THE MATCH OF THE CENTURY,

31:31.150 --> 31:34.153
THE ONE YOU'VE BEEN AVOIDING
ALL THESE YEARS.

31:34.283 --> 31:37.286
YOU... AGAINST ME.

31:37.939 --> 31:39.985
BRUNO'S RESTAURANT.
ONE HOUR.

32:01.180 --> 32:02.485
-HEY.

32:16.543 --> 32:17.892
-BRANSON!

32:23.115 --> 32:24.420
-SO, WHAT'S IT
GONNA BE, BUCHANNON?

32:25.813 --> 32:28.250
ARE YOU GONNA FIGHT ME NOW
OR DO I BREAK HIS LEG?

32:29.686 --> 32:31.384
-SOUNDS LIKE YOUR BOSS
JUST WALKED IN.

32:31.514 --> 32:33.647
TOO BAD HE'S GONNA HAVE
TO BE CARRIED OUT.

32:34.430 --> 32:35.954
-LET HIM GO!

32:36.084 --> 32:37.433
COME ON. COME ON.

32:42.090 --> 32:43.831
WHERE'S SUMMER?
-IN THE KITCHEN.

32:43.962 --> 32:45.615
THEY SAID THEY'D HURT HER
IF I DIDN'T FIGHT.

32:45.746 --> 32:48.705
-OUT WITH THE OLD...
IN WITH THE NEW!

32:49.315 --> 32:51.273
COME ON, PAL. YOU'RE NEXT!

32:51.404 --> 32:53.449
-JUST LET HIM GO.
-NO, I WANT TO MAKE SURE
YOU STAY MOTIVATED.

32:54.015 --> 32:55.930
AND THEY'LL BE NO MPS
TO CALL THIS TIME.

32:56.061 --> 32:57.105
-LET HIM GO, FIRST.

33:27.222 --> 33:29.964
-HEY, COME ON, UP! COME ON!
UP, UP, UP! GET UP!

33:31.183 --> 33:32.271
-GET UP! GET UP!

33:57.861 --> 33:59.515
-COME ON, COME ON.

34:39.773 --> 34:42.688
-[PEOPLE APPLAUD]

34:50.130 --> 34:52.612
-ANY TIME YOU WANT
TO FIGHT AGAIN,
PLEASE LET ME KNOW.

34:52.742 --> 34:53.786
-HERE.

34:53.917 --> 34:55.527
THAT'S THE LEAST HE OWES YOU.

34:55.658 --> 34:57.617
IF I EVER FIND OUT YOU'RE
HAVING THESE FIGHTS HERE,

34:57.747 --> 34:59.358
OR ANYWHERE ELSE,

34:59.488 --> 35:01.316
I'LL SHOW UP WITH CUSTOMERS
YOU WON'T WANT TO KNOW.

35:16.549 --> 35:17.680
-ARE YOU GUYS OKAY?

35:18.812 --> 35:20.596
-WE'VE HAD BETTER DAYS.
-YEAH, I'LL SAY.

35:22.685 --> 35:24.165
ARE YOU OKAY?
DID THEY HURT YOU?

35:24.296 --> 35:26.080
-NO. CAN WE JUST
GET OUT OF HERE?

35:26.211 --> 35:28.038
-THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

35:28.169 --> 35:29.127
COME ON.

36:47.205 --> 36:50.512
WELL, I GUESS THAT'S
WHAT THEY MEAN BY...

36:51.296 --> 36:52.210
DEAD WEIGHT.

36:53.733 --> 36:54.603
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

37:03.525 --> 37:06.311
-C.J., WHAT ARE YOU
STILL DOING HERE?

37:07.834 --> 37:10.271
-I'M ON DUTY.
-C.J., LOOK AT ME.

37:11.272 --> 37:13.231
-I CAN'T. I HAVE
TO WATCH MY WATER.

37:13.970 --> 37:15.798
-C.J., WE LEAVE
FOR PUERTO RICO
IN THREE HOURS

37:15.929 --> 37:17.017
TO SHOOT THE COVER.

37:17.800 --> 37:20.063
-I KNOW, BUT I HAVE
TO FINISH MY SHIFT.

37:20.194 --> 37:22.022
I'M RESPONSIBLE FOR
EVERYBODY ON THIS BEACH.

37:22.936 --> 37:24.720
-C.J., I AM ON THIS BEACH,

37:25.808 --> 37:27.897
AND YOU HAVE RESPONSIBILITIES
TO ME, AS WELL.

37:28.724 --> 37:30.770
-WELL, YEAH, BUT YOU'RE NOT
IN ANY DANGER OF DROWNING.

37:32.075 --> 37:33.338
-YES, I AM, C.J.

37:35.557 --> 37:37.167
I AM DROWNING
IN MY LOVE FOR YOU.

38:50.023 --> 38:51.154
THIS IS A DISASTER!

38:52.504 --> 38:55.158
C.J., I CAN'T POSTPONE THE SHOOT
UNTIL YOUR FACE HEALS.

38:55.289 --> 38:57.335
YOU SHOULD HAVE GOTTEN
SOMEONE ELSE TO DO THIS.

38:58.510 --> 38:59.946
WHY DID YOU LET HER
SCRATCH YOU?

39:00.076 --> 39:02.252
-ALAIN, DON'T BE ABSURD.
SHE COULD HAVE DIED.

39:02.383 --> 39:04.559
-I HAVE NEWS FOR YOU.
SO COULD THIS PROJECT.

39:04.690 --> 39:07.867
YOUR FOCUS IS SPLIT.
WHERE IS YOUR COMMITMENT?

39:09.042 --> 39:10.217
-CAN WE TALK ABOUT THIS LATER?

39:10.348 --> 39:11.653
I HAVE TO MAKE OUT
A RESCUE REPORT.

39:11.784 --> 39:13.394
-NO, C.J., NO.

39:13.525 --> 39:15.483
MAYBE I CAN COVER THOSE MARKS UP
WITH SPECIAL MAKE-UP.

39:17.180 --> 39:18.356
C.J., COME WITH ME.

39:19.574 --> 39:21.054
-WHAT IF I DECIDE NOT TO GO?

39:22.664 --> 39:24.144
WHAT HAPPENS TO US?

39:25.450 --> 39:27.016
-THERE IS NO US.

39:28.322 --> 39:30.933
-ARE YOU SAYING IF WE HAVE
NO PROFESSIONAL RELATIONSHIP,

39:31.064 --> 39:33.240
THAT WE HAVE
NO RELATIONSHIP AT ALL?

39:33.371 --> 39:36.461
-C.J., THEY ARE INSEPARABLE.
THEY'RE THE SAME.

39:37.070 --> 39:39.377
YOU'LL BE BY MY SIDE
BOTH IN WORK AND PLEASURE.

39:40.029 --> 39:41.161
THAT IS THE WAY I AM.

39:42.597 --> 39:44.469
-WELL, WHAT IF I'M NOT RIGHT
FOR THE NEXT JOB?

39:46.601 --> 39:48.908
DOES THE NEW MODEL TAKE MY PLACE
IN BOTH WORK AND PLEASURE?

39:49.517 --> 39:50.736
-C.J., THIS IS CRAZY.

39:52.302 --> 39:53.739
DON'T THROW YOUR LIFE AWAY
ON THE BEACH,

39:53.869 --> 39:55.349
WORKING FOR PEANUTS,

39:55.480 --> 39:59.397
WHEN YOU CAN HAVE GLAMOUR,
PRESTIGE, AND ME.

40:01.094 --> 40:02.530
WHAT IS YOUR DECISION?

40:04.271 --> 40:06.229
-WELL, THIS MIGHT BE HARD
FOR YOU TO UNDERSTAND, ALAIN,

40:07.274 --> 40:09.319
BUT I REALLY LOVE
BEING A LIFEGUARD.

40:10.059 --> 40:12.148
I KNOW I DON'T MAKE
VERY MUCH MONEY...

40:13.106 --> 40:14.890
BUT SAVING THAT LITTLE GIRL
RIGHT NOW...

40:16.109 --> 40:17.545
THAT GAVE ME MORE FULFILLMENT...

40:18.372 --> 40:22.637
THAN GLAMOUR OR PRESTIGE
OR YOU EVER COULD.

40:26.859 --> 40:28.991
-YOU'RE GOING TO THROW AWAY
EVERYTHING I'VE DONE FOR YOU?

40:29.122 --> 40:31.429
-NO, I'M NOT GONNA THROW
ANY OF IT AWAY.

40:34.562 --> 40:36.912
YOU MADE ME REALIZE
WHO I REALLY AM.

40:39.741 --> 40:41.787
I'LL CHERISH EVERYTHING
THAT YOU'VE DONE FOR ME.

40:46.052 --> 40:47.183
I'VE GOT TO GET BACK TO WORK.

40:57.106 --> 40:57.977
GOODBYE, ALAIN.

41:06.725 --> 41:08.204
-MAN: SHE'S OUT TAKING A SWIM.

41:10.729 --> 41:11.904
-I THINK YOU DID
THE RIGHT THING.

41:13.340 --> 41:14.559
-THAT'S WHAT I KEEP
TELLING MYSELF.

41:16.169 --> 41:18.476
SO, I HEAR YOU'RE REAL HANDY
WITH A FRYING PAN.

41:18.606 --> 41:21.566
-OH, YEAH.
I'M A REAL KNOCKOUT
IN THE KITCHEN.

41:21.696 --> 41:22.958
-YOU KNOW,
I SHOULD'VE BEEN THERE.

41:23.655 --> 41:25.787
HOW'S STEVE DOING?
-OH, GOOD.

41:25.918 --> 41:28.311
I FOUND HIM AN APARTMENT,
AND MITCH FOUND HIM A NEW COACH.

41:28.442 --> 41:29.965
-WHO?
-ME.

41:30.531 --> 41:31.489
